-- ds.h3: How to create a custom tiro-font type? 

-- ds.markdown: 

How to use `ftd.type` to create a custom font `types` using tiro-font? 

We don't recommend creating custom types. We recommend to use 
our [tiro-typography](https://fastn-community.github.io/tiro-typography)

If you're using [tiro-typography](https://fastn-community.github.io/tiro-typography) 
and still your designer has introduced new font size which is not included or 
part of our [tiro-typography](https://fastn-community.github.io/tiro-typography) 
then only define custom types. 

We hope you shouldn't need to define a custom type.

Below is an example of creating a custom `ftd.type` using tiro-font.

-- ds.rendered:

-- ds.rendered.input:

\-- ftd.type tiro-font-size-12-desktop:
size.px: 12
weight: 400
font-family: $tiro-font-assets.fonts.Tiro


\-- ftd.type tiro-font-size-12-mobile:
size.px: 12
weight: 400
font-family: $tiro-font-assets.fonts.Tiro

\-- ftd.responsive-type tiro-font-size-12-400:
desktop: $tiro-font-size-12-desktop
mobile: $tiro-font-size-12-mobile

\-- ftd.text: 
